# newsyslog(8) rotation config for Zeus Gateway (macOS)
# Installed by scripts/install.sh into /etc/newsyslog.d/com.zeus.gateway.conf
#
# Format: logfile owner:group mode count size when flags [pid_file] [sig_num]
#   count  = keep 5 archived generations
#   size   = rotate when log exceeds threshold (KB)
#   flags  = J = bzip2 compress, Z = gzip compress
#   Z      = gzip (newsyslog default, widely supported)
#
# Thresholds tuned for gateway I/O patterns:
#   - gateway.log (stdout + info+ tracing; daily rotation is owned in-process, #321 — this is a size backstop) → 50 MB
#   - error.log (stderr + warn+ tracing) → 10 MB
#
# Regression fence: if you change log paths in the plist template,
# update this file AND the install.sh cleanup stanza.
__LOG_DIR__/gateway.log  __USER__:admin  644  5  51200  *  Z
__LOG_DIR__/error.log  __USER__:admin  644  5  10240  *  Z
